From the article, the only <i>really</i> nasty things are:<p><pre><code>  [a].forEach(fn(){})
  [b].forEach(fn(){})
  // Parses as [a][b]

  return
  a+b
  // Parses as return;
</code></pre>
You would have to work pretty hard to trigger the rest.<p>I'm curious about the speed trade offs from removing semicolons. You shrink the source code a little, but does the parser throwing exceptions all the time bump up execution time?
